 one time, but at that time I also had a seperate box with Windows on it, so I didn't feel the need.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Like a lot of the sort of homemade hardware that might come from tinkerers on this forum. Notice that a lot of what retrousb.com sells is "obscure pieces of hardware" such as the CopyNES kit.</div>
