		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Like a lot of the sort of homemade hardware that might come from tinkerers on this forum. Notice that a lot of what retrousb.com sells is "obscure pieces of hardware" such as the CopyNES kit.</div><br />I find it hard to believe that those don't work on Windows.</div>
<br />Windows XP, the 32-bit version of Windows Vista, and the 32-bit version of Windows 7 will load drivers without a verifiable Authenticode digital signature. The 64-bit version of Windows Vista and the 64-bit version of Windows 7 will not. <a href="http://www.google.com/search?q=windows+kernel+mode+code+signing" class="postlink">Google explains</a>.
